{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7,"isBulletin":133},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Tavole greche de'magistrati annuali, scoperte ultimamente fra le rovine dell'antichissima città di Acre in Sicilia","Amati","1827","\u003Cspan>Girolamo Amati, «Tavole greche de’magistrati annuali, scoperte ultimamente fra le rovine dell’antichissima città di Acre in Sicilia», \u003Ci>Giornale Arcadico di scienze, lettere, ed arti\u003C/i> 35 (1827): 339–57, \u003Ca href=\"https://ia800903.us.archive.org/12/items/giornalearcadico35roma/giornalearcadico35roma.pdf\">https://ia800903.us.archive.org/12/items/giornalearcadico35roma/giornalearcadico35roma.pdf\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/7CXM4Y52",[8],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":28,"handNote":37,"date":57,"places":62,"geo":72,"provenance":64,"provenanceGeo":76,"country":77,"region":78,"settlement":68,"repository":79,"idno":83,"textLang":86,"tmNumber":90,"facsimile":91,"letterHeights":98,"publications":104,"zotero":110,"keywords":116,"html":126,"bibl":127,"citedRangeSort":128,"languageSort":87,"materialSort":23,"typeSort":15},"ISic001031","Dedication recording board of magistrates",{"_":12},"draft",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"dedication; list of magistrates","#function.dedication #function.list.magistrates","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.htm",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"ana":27},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":29},{"p":30,"rs":31,"damage":35},"Line 1 is inscribed across the upper moulding (which is heavily damaged); the remainder of the text is engraved on the recessed front face, in two columns. The spacing between the columns after the first line is very irregular; column 2 has a half-line gap after line 2, meaning that the lines in the two columns are vertically out of synch after this point.",{"_":32,"ana":33,"ref":34},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":36},"#text_condition.partly_illegible",{"lettering":38,"dimensions":39},"Neatly carved and regular letters, mostly without serifs, but some terminal wedges. Alpha with straight bar; epsilon on occasion has a slightly shorter mid-bar; zeta in form of I with wide horizontals; theta has short detached cross-bar; kappa has full-length arms; mu has vertical first and last, full length mid-strokes; xsi has three equal horiztonal bars; omicron is only slightly smaller than the other letters; pi has extended horizontal; rho has small rounded closed eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom, with slihgtly variable mid-strokes; phi has small oval eye, with vertical often extended; omega is notably variable, always closed, but ranging from tear-drop to full circle on or even above and detached from the base line.",[40,46,53],{"type":41,"l":42,"from":43,"to":43,"h":44,"unit":45,"atLeast":44,"atMost":44},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","18","mm",{"type":41,"l":47,"from":48,"to":49,"h":50,"unit":45,"atLeast":51,"atMost":52},"Line 2-23","line2","line23","11-15 (with omicron down to 9 and phi up to 20)","11","15",{"type":54,"l":55,"from":56,"to":48,"unit":45},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line",{"_":58,"notBefore":59,"notAfter":60,"evidence":61},"Later third or second century BCE on palaeographic grounds.",-250,-101,"lettering",[63,67],{"_":64,"type":65,"ref":66},"Acrae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462068",{"_":68,"type":69,"ref":70,"offset":71},"Palazzolo Acreide","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2523922","near",[73],[74,75],37.0578,14.89346,[],"Italy","Sicily",{"_":80,"role":81,"ref":82},"Museo Archeologico Gabriele 